ilds an incisive case for a return to critical, open inquiry as a guiding principle for the future public health we want—and a future we must work to protect.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCOVID-19 (Disease)zUnited StatesxInfluence. 0aLiberalismzUnited States. 0aPolitics, Practical. 0aPublic healthxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aPublic healthxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPublic health. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226828862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226828862/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles